title.narrative: Undergraduate programs elaborated according to LMD with complete description
Universities with performance-based contracts negotiated and overseen by GHED
Tertiary institutions with a Board of Director (Conseil d'Administration) that approves the annual budget
Students enrolled in programs designed with private sector in the ISEP
Teachers having followed training in the LMD requirements for teaching
Institutions that achieve at least 80% of the annual targets set in the performance-based contracts
Budget allocated based on performance-based contracts
Academic programs that meet the minimum quality standard as set
Repeating students in year 1 in UCAD
All tertiary education institutions use the new financial law to manage their budget
Annual tertiary education statistics report produced
GDHE is implemented to (i) coordinate the implementation of the tertiary education program, (ii) provide oversight for PBC implementation, and (iii) monitor the status of reforms
Promotion rate at grade one by university
